The paper discusses the use of Remotely Piloted Aircrafts (RPA) as 5G points of presence, which involves the integration of mobile nodes into the 5G infrastructure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the feasibility and cost of using virtualisation techniques over resource-constrained aerial vehicle platforms, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of RPAs in emergency cases, which could be related to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the Architecture (cs.AR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories, as it discusses the integration of RPAs into the 5G infrastructure and the potential security implications of using these platforms.
